Selenium = Programming Language(Java) + Element Locators(HTML)

Anything that we see on a web page, we call it web element
Element Locator: Its a way(technique) to locate the address of any web element on a web page

Xpath: Using Xpath we can get the address of any web element

HTML: Hyper Text Mark-up Language

<tagName attribute1 = "value" attribute2 ="value2"..........attributeN="valueN"/>
<tagName attribute1 = "value" attribute2 ="value2"..........attributeN="valueN"></tagName>
<tagName attribute1 = "value" attribute2 ="value2"..........attributeN="valueN">innerText</tagName>


<input type="text" name="email" value="" placeholder="E-Mail" id="input-email" class="form-control">

tagName = input
how many attributes are there= 6
id = input-email
name = email
placeholder = E-Mail
"" = value
form-control = class

value = nameOfAttribute ?
innerText

<input type="password" name="password" value="" placeholder="Password" id="input-password" class="form-control">

